karn@qualcom.qualcomm.com (Phil Karn) writes:

>Not that I doubt his integrity, of course, but do I REALLY want to
>take the chance that there ISN'T a trapdoor in DISKREET (for whatever
>purpose) when I can easily protect myself with public domain
>encryption code whose complete source code can be freely examined and
>recompiled?

A side note: there is a nicely implemented public domain on-the-fly
file compressor for MS-DOS called DietDisk (not to be confused with
similarly named shareware/commercial products).  Comes with assembly
source.  Some enterprising person could marry that with DES....
